LET'S GET READY TO REBEL!! The Lady Rebels Volleyball Team are playing in Kulm tonight against South Border starting at 5PM! Come on out and cheer them on!

Rebel Fans- will enter the school using door E1 and sit on the East bleachers. Fans will be required to wear a mask while inside our building.

Visiting Fans- will enter the school using door E1 and sit on the West bleachers. Fans will be required to wear a mask while inside our building.

Concessions (Limited menu quantities) will be located in the school commons. No tables will be used. Fans will take all food items back to their seat and eat them there.

Restrooms will be available.

All Fans are asked to leave the gym and school in a timely manner after the match is over. Please wait for athletes or others outside of the building.

THUNDER NATION, LETS GET READY TO RUMBLE!! August 21st, 2020 the EEK Thunder will be hosting the Carrington Cardinals at the Kulm Football Field at 7pm! Come on out and cheer on the boys! $6 for adults and $4 for students at the gate. Thunder passes are available this year, please come by the school office if you would like one.
-Please practice social distancing at this event. -Masks are encouraged for all spectators.
-First come parking will be allowed around the field with handicapped parking on the West end zone. -Please leave space for spectators to walk between your vehicles and the field rope.
-No bleachers will be available at the game. Concessions will be available with limited menu and quantities.
-You can also catch the game on BEK & KSJB radio

post_text: The Kulm Public School District School Board invites the public to participate in a school demographic planning meeting to fulfill requirements under NDCC Section 15.1-07-26. This open public meeting will be held on 6/15/2020 at 7:00 pm via Zoom (Please contact the school office for login information). At this forum, the school board will discuss and receive public input on how three- and five-year demographics may impact academic and extracurricular programs, instructional and administrative staffing, facility needs and utilization, district tax levies, and the district‚Äôs strategic plan.

shared_text:
ADAPT Training
March 30 at 6:38 PM ¬∑

CALLING ALL ATHLETES!

ADAPT for POWER

Power is the combination of all aspects of athleticism being utilized in a single action.

Many Sports and Athletes mistake pure strength training for Power development.

1) Function (Natural Mechanics)

- The ability for the muscular system to respond in an optimal sequence to perform a task

2) Efficiency. (Strength, Quickness, Reaction, Speed, Flexibility, and Endurance)

- Coordination of all athletic characteristics

3) Performance (Neuromuscular)

- Maximize muscular effectiveness with a learned skill, as well as a reactive response.

True athletic Power can only be developed with an understanding of every aspect of muscular performance!

Contact marissa@adapttraining.com with any questions or for custom programs.

The past few days have been difficult for everyone with the widespread closures and cancellations of many events and activities. We recognize that you may have questions and be wondering what comes next. There are some things we don‚Äôt know the answer to, but here‚Äôs what we do know right now.

1. School will be in session tomorrow, Monday, March 16th. Although the surrounding states of Minnesota and South Dakota have made announcements to call off school, in ND there is still only 1 confirmed case and no evidence of community spread.
2. As of Friday, the ND High School Activities Association has suspended spring extra-curricular activities including both practices and contests. If anything changes regarding that, we will send that information out as soon as we get it.

Please see the attached documents for more information regarding the KPS response to COVID-19.

On Friday, March 13, due to the Emergency Declaration issued by President Trump the NDHSAA will suspend play at the 2020 NDHSAA Class A Basketball State Tournament and all remaining 2020 NDHSAA Winter Postseason State Tournaments including the 2020 NDHSAA Class B Boys Basketball State Tournament.

In addition to the remaining 2020 NDHSAA Winter Postseason Basketball State Tournaments being suspended, all remaining fine arts and spring sports seasons have been suspended indefinitely, which includes practices and game contests. Further information will be released as it becomes available.

Refund Policies for 2020 NDHSAA Class A Basketball State Tournament and 2020 NDHSAA Class B Boys Basketball State Tournament will be announced at a later date on www.ndhsaanow.com.
